This paper deals with image and video deblurring using deep learning techniques, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also proposes a convolutional neural network (CNN)-based down-scaling method, which involves training a neural network to learn kernels for down-scaling, which falls under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The use of deep neural networks for deblurring also involves optimization and training of the network, which falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also involves experiments and evaluations on datasets, which falls under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves image processing techniques, which falls under the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
